<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1268830-does-this-novel-have-anything-about-the">Does this novel have anything about the British rule in India? Does this talk about how Indians were suppressed and tortured by the malicious ways British followed to suppress the fight for freedom?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1268830'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F146746.The_Jewel_in_the_Crown">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1268830-does-this-novel-have-anything-about-the">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1268830-does-this-novel-have-anything-about-the">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/45983110-kevin-carlson"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/45983110-kevin-carlson">Kevin Carlson</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I would say the it does an adequate job of describing the suppression and torture during the last 5 years of the Raj (or British occupation, as I call<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I would say the it does an adequate job of describing the suppression and torture during the last 5 years of the Raj (or British occupation, as I call it). However, it does not address inter-sectarian violence before the occupation started or since it ended. Be at ease, though. Sectarian violence is not unique to India and has been present in human society as far back as one cares to look. Sadly, this is not likely to change in my lifetime.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

