<div id="review_44152990" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/44152990" />
    <a title="Catherine  Mustread" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1894763-catherine-mustread"><img alt="Catherine  Mustread" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1236519005p2/1894763.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/44152990?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Catherine  Mustread" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Catherine  Mustread" href="/user/show/1894763-catherine-mustread">Catherine  Mustread</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Catherine  by: </span>
      Conde Nast Traveler top 69 fiction travel books
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1894763-catherine-mustread?shelf=british">british</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1894763-catherine-mustread?shelf=india">india</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1894763-catherine-mustread?shelf=historical">historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1894763-catherine-mustread?shelf=1930s">1930s</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1894763-catherine-mustread?shelf=1940s">1940s</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer44152990" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15183208041438913820">Though this book ranks high on the literary scale, and as a subject of interest-- India at the end of the British era, 1930-40s, I got tired of reading it long before the end. Scott gives so many viewpoints of the same event, it was difficult for me to continue turning the pages. Mixed feelings about continuing the series. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


